==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Music hall
<hw>Music hall</hw>. <def>A place for public musical entertainments;
specif. (<mark>Eng.</mark>), esp. a public hall for vaudeville
performances, in which smoking and drinking are usually allowed in the
auditorium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

